(1) Hospitalization + supportive care: NPO, NG decompression if megacolon, IV fluid, electrolyte correction (K), VTE prophylaxis (UC = high VTE risk), correct anemia, nutritional support (parenteral if needed); rule out CDI + CMV (stool toxin + sigmoidoscopy biopsy CMV IHC);

