Meconium ileus in neonate — likely cystic fibrosis-associated:

(1) Initial resuscitation: NPO, NG decompression, IV fluid, broad-spectrum antibiotic;

(2) Cystic fibrosis evaluation — sweat chloride test + CFTR genetic testing — > 80% of meconium ileus have CF; refer pulmonology, genetics;

