Diabetic foot ulcer + osteomyelitis — multimodal:

(1) Hospitalization for moderate-severe infection;

(2) IV broad-spectrum antibiotic cover MRSA + gram-negative + anaerobes — vancomycin + cefepime or pip-tazo; tailor per culture (deep tissue or bone biopsy preferred); long course 4-6 weeks for osteomyelitis (IV → oral switch acceptable when stable);

(3) Glycemic control strict — IV insulin or aggressive sliding scale; target 140-180;

(4) Surgical debridement + bone resection (toe amputation in this case); send bone for culture + histopathology;

(5) Wound care: NPWT consider, offloading (total contact cast — gold standard but contraindicated active infection; alternatives: removable cast walker, crutches);

(6) Revascularization assessment: ABI normal but TBI/PVR for microvascular DM; vascular consult if pulses absent or non-healing;

(7) Diabetes management comprehensive: nutrition, education, foot care, eye exam, renal monitoring;

(8) Multidisciplinary team: vascular, podiatry, infectious disease, endocrinology, wound care, nutrition;

(9) Long-term: prevent recurrence (foot care, footwear, surveillance), high-risk for recurrence + contralateral involvement;

(10) WIfI score (Wound, Ischemia, foot Infection) — stratifies + guides intervention
